{
  "texts": [
    "By integrating generative models like GANs with CNNs, hybrid networks leverage the strengths of both GANs' ability to generate realistic data and CNNs' proficiency in extracting hierarchical features.",
    "Jaiswal and Gupta (2023) present GANs and LSTM hybrid classification framework.",
    "The authors developed a GAN combined with a Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) model, referred to as GLSTM, for classifying diabetes using both real and synthetic data.",
    "The GAN generates the synthetic data to augment the training dataset, addressing data scarcity and privacy issues in medical datasets.",
    "The LSTM model handles sequential data to perform classification."
  ]
}